      <fr:p>Both (i) and (ii) follow from the general theory (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9.xml" taxon="Scholium" number="8.1.9" />).
        To prove (iii), we contemplate <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.19" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.19.xml" number="8.1.19" /> and note that the Hodge structures <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^p(\widetilde {Y}_q^r,\varepsilon _\mathbb {Q}^r)[-r]]]></fr:tex> (for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+q+r=n]]></fr:tex>) satisfy (iii).
        To prove (iv), we note that the Hodge structures <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^p(X_q)]]></fr:tex> (for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p+q=n]]></fr:tex>) satisfy (iv).</fr:p>
